Add to the repo:

git add 'file_name'
git commit -m "First Commit"


Checking status:

git status


Making Changes:

git status (to check what change where made)
git add hello.txt
git status


Commit (like making a snapshot of our work):

git commit -m “Add Readme.txt”



Upload to the project(GIT):

git push

~~~~~~~~~~ Various ~~~~~~~~~~~

Remove file:
git rm file


Rename (only by moving)
git mv oldShit newShit
git add -u newShit
commit

git add -A  {stages All}
git add .   {stages new and modified, without deleted}
git add -u  {stages modified and deleted, without new}